<br>
Ok, with this being true and considering the advantage of reducing damage the meatshield warrior takes with a shield.  The Meatshield warrior will essentially take considerably &quot;more&quot; damage than the MT.  At this point you need a CH rotation on not only the MT but the Meatshield as well.<br>
<br>
Now, let's talk about this Meatshield rotation that some of you have come up with.  Seeing how this ability will only last for 36 seconds and has a reuse time that is still yet to be announced.  A Meatshield rotation will require 3 or 4 additional warriors on a raid each taking &quot;more&quot; damage than the MT on their own turn.<br>
<br>
So in reality we will be putting our least equipped warriors up front to MT with high aggro weapons.  While our beafcake warriors that are packed with HP are going to set up a Meatshield rotation.  Durring which several announcements will be made requiring all clerics in said rotation to change targets and start a rotation on a different Warrior.  Meanwhile we have the gimpy up front getting pounded and praying to god he stays alive while trying to hold aggro.<br>
<br>
This sounds like a nightmare to me.  One could ponder the tatctics all they like to find a usefull situation for this but in the end it shave the ass of what we call MT encounters and teaches them to walk backwards.  Pretty ugly if you ask me. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=193604" target=new><font size=5 face="arial, helvetica, sans-serif" color=darkred>Keelz Neversleep</font></a><BR><font size=2 face="arial, helvetica, sans-serif"><I>
