Well, the answer is yes and no.  The shaman spell will do a maximum of 1900 HP or heal up to 75%, which ever is lesser.  The druid spell will do a maximum of 2900 or heal up to 75%, which ever is lesser.  (going off memory here, the I'm rounding, not quoting exact figures)<br>
<br>
These spells will be useful in spot healing.  However, when you're talking a plate melee type with 6k+ HP who is getting beat on for 700-1100 points a smack, they are only going to be marginally useful.  They may help bridge the gap between CHs, certainly that seems likely, or used in tandem together with several others on a Warrior using meatshield, that might work too.  But its going to take very careful coordination.<br>
<br>
Will they figure into a strategy using meatshield?  Maybe, it could happen.  I see that as pretty difficult to pull off though, under most circumstances, but hey who knows?<br>
