This means that the healing rotation will have to rotate to different warriors, but that also means that a warrior is essential to every group, and aggro is absolutely essential to the main tank.<br>
<br>
This makes sense as a warrior won't be able to reduce the amount of damage a mob does, and the key warrior to be healed will still need to be healed in the same manner and speed that they are healed today. <br>
I doubt that Verant intended Meatshield to reduce the damage over time to a single warrior so that it would be easier to tank mobs.<br>
<br>
If Meatshield is used in this way, then twarriors will be essential to a guild and to all raids. It wouldn't matter whether an SK is the main tank or a warrior, as long as there is a warrior in the same group as the SK is in. However, it will matter that you have a warrior in each group to actually take the damage from the mobs. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ushelrabbi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shelrabbi</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 233<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/11/02 11:09:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2137.topic&index=39>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Faster fights mean less rotations</span><hr size=1> Didn't read the whole thing, but I bet this ability turns out to be great and warriors who can use it in a timely fashion will be heralded as heroes.<br>
